// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p07/fail.test — P7 violation: a float literal
// produced by a `#define` body crosses the preprocessor → lexer
// seam without a `_int(...)` reduction. Per FR-019 + the FR-037
// locked-string table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`,
// this is detected at the seam and emits:
//
// FR-037 P7 lock:  `float literal cannot cross the preprocessor seam`
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII the failing fixture asserts the
// EXACT diagnostic string. Renaming or weakening it later requires a
// contract amendment in `contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`
// PLUS this fixture's update in the same change.
//
// Source: a `#define` body whose final reduction is a real-typed
// `PPValue` (not `_int(...)`-coerced); the substitution into
// `reg x = %F%` would emit a float literal token, which the
// preprocessor MUST reject at the seam (P12 invariant: no float
// literals at the seam).
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer
// tokenizes `_real(8)/2.0` literally and exits 0 (the float source
// bytes lex per §13 as integer + dot + integer; no preprocessor
// exists). Phase-4 wires the seam check.

// RUN: echo '#define F _real(8) / 2.0' > %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg x = %%F%%;'           >> %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING — exact match:
// CHECK: error: float literal cannot cross the preprocessor seam
